article.headline: IUPUI 69, W. Illinois 47
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Gary Patterson's 30 points accounted for nearly half of IUPUI's scoring in a 69-47 victory over Western Illinois on Saturday. Patterson shot 11-of-17 from the floor and was 6-of-11 from 3-point range. The Jaguars (12-12, 5-5 Mid-Continent Conference) finished 10-of-18 (55 percent) from behind the arc. David Barlow added 16 points and Billy Pettiford had eight points for IUPUI. Troy Okeson and Morris Smith led the Leathernecks (6-20, 2-9) with eight points each. Western Illinois was outrebounded 36-24. The Leathernecks were called for 22 fouls which IUPUI turned into 17 points at the free throw line.
